        {
            "_comment": "P-66.4.1 / P-65.3.1.4: carboximidic acid R-C(=NH)-OH, the imido (=O->=NH) analog of the carboxylic acid. PIN suffixes '-imidic acid' (terminal, on a chain stem: ethanimidic acid CC(=N)O) and '-carboximidic acid' (nonterminal, on a ring: benzenecarboximidic acid N=C(O)c1ccccc1). Anchor on the central C. The imido N is [NX2;!R] H1 (=NH) or H0 (N-substituted, e.g. N-methylethanimidic acid CN=C(C)O); the !R bars an ENDOCYCLIC C=N (e.g. 2-hydroxy-3,4,5,6-tetrahydropyridine OC1=NCCCC1, a cyclic enol/imine, not a carboximidic acid). Also excluded are =N-OH (hydroximic acid, handled by the acid-infix composer) and =N-NH2 (hydrazonic acid). The multiplied chain form '-diimidic acid' is not OPSIN-expressible, so the engine skips this PCG for 2+ chain instances (see engine.py guard) and falls back to the dihydroxy...diimine prefix form. Carbamimidic acid H2N-C(=NH)-OH names substitutively as aminomethanimidic acid (the NH2 becomes the amino prefix) and carbonimidic acid HO-C(=NH)-OH as hydroxymethanimidic acid -- both OPSIN PIN-round-trip. Subsumes the imine (C=NH) + alcohol/phenol (OH) it overlaps so the combined characteristic group is the single acid suffix instead of split imine+ol prefixes.",
